Settlement and Removal: Poor Relief and Exclusion in 18th-century London

Sharon Howard
May 2017

St Clement Danes

The sources

  • Settlement, bastardy and vagrancy examinations (1739-1800)
  • Register of removal orders (1752-93)
  • Appeals to Sessions of the Peace (1690-1799)

Linkage, 1753-92

  • 5046 examinations and 2479 orders
  • 2357 orders (95%) could be linked to at least 1 examination (75% of unlinkable orders were vagrancy orders)
  • 44 petitions to Middlesex Sessions
